239
00:11:41.326 --> 00:11:43.577
The night Maya died.
didn't have an alibi.

240
00:11:43.578 --> 00:11:45.495
Then it comes out
he was having an affair. so...

241
00:11:45.496 --> 00:11:47.581
You're leaving out
the part about a cigarette butt

242
00:11:47.582 --> 00:11:48.832
that was found in the car
with his wife's body.

243
00:11:48.833 --> 00:11:50.709
DNA wasn't a match.

244
00:11:50.710 --> 00:11:52.669
Bill. you and I both know
he could have picked up

245
00:11:52.670 --> 00:11:54.421
any butt from any gutter

246
00:11:54.422 --> 00:11:55.714
and put it in the car
to throw off forensics.

247
00:11:55.715 --> 00:11:57.966
Detective Ragsdale.

248
00:11:57.967 --> 00:12:00.218
are you aware you're associating
with a known felon right now?

249
00:12:00.219 --> 00:12:01.178
Detective Abreu. hello.
How are you?

250
00:12:01.179 --> 00:12:02.971
Yeah. let me guess.

251
00:12:02.972 --> 00:12:04.473
He wants us to put cuffs
on Clay Gregory for this.

252
00:12:04.474 --> 00:12:05.724
Well. I mean.
it'd be nice if you put cuffs

253
00:12:05.725 --> 00:12:06.934
on him for <i>something.</i>

254
00:12:06.935 --> 00:12:08.518
Mm-hmm.
Just a reminder.

255
00:12:08.519 --> 00:12:10.354
my case. not yours.

256
00:12:10.355 --> 00:12:12.564
And sharing information
with a civilian.

257
00:12:12.565 --> 00:12:15.400
let alone an ex-con.
would be bad.
Hm.

258
00:12:15.401 --> 00:12:16.652
How is everything
at the trailer park?

259
00:12:16.653 --> 00:12:17.903
You making new friends?

260
00:12:17.904 --> 00:12:19.655
Only every single day.

261
00:12:23.493 --> 00:12:25.911
Clay Gregory didn't
kill anyone last night.

262
00:12:25.912 --> 00:12:27.162
What do you mean?

263
00:12:27.163 --> 00:12:28.664
He was visiting family
in Topeka.

264
00:12:28.665 --> 00:12:30.248
Flew in this morning.

265
00:12:30.249 --> 00:12:32.542
We have footage of him
at both airports.

266
00:12:32.543 --> 00:12:35.295
So if you were hoping <i>this</i> was
the murder we would get him on.

267
00:12:35.296 --> 00:12:36.505
think again.

268
00:12:44.013 --> 00:12:46.765
News Achor:
<i>When asked about the still
unsolved Maya Gregory case.</i>

269
00:12:46.766 --> 00:12:49.351
<i>police did acknowledge
the similarities to the murder</i>

270
00:12:49.352 --> 00:12:50.769
<i>of Rhoda Batista.</i>

271
00:12:50.770 --> 00:12:53.188
<i>By all accounts.</i>

272
00:12:53.189 --> 00:12:56.149
<i>Clay Gregory is apparently</i> not
<i>a person of interest at this--</i>

273
00:13:08.746 --> 00:13:10.289
Decker Investigations.

274
00:13:10.290 --> 00:13:11.748
<i>Hi. Is this RJ Decker?</i>

275
00:13:11.749 --> 00:13:13.333
Yep. It is.
<i>Great.</i>

276
00:13:13.334 --> 00:13:15.460
<i>I'm looking for
a private investigator.</i>

277
00:13:15.461 --> 00:13:17.421
<i>I was wondering if you
might have some time this week</i>

278
00:13:17.422 --> 00:13:19.423
<i>to meet in person to--

279
00:13:19.424 --> 00:13:20.674
<i>long-term work--</i>

280
00:13:20.675 --> 00:13:22.676
Ma'am. I'm sorry.
Bad reception.

281
00:13:22.677 --> 00:13:24.679
Would you mind repeating
what you just said. ma'am?

282
00:13:28.016 --> 00:13:30.309
<i>Are you there.
Mr. Decker?</i>

283
00:13:30.310 --> 00:13:32.644
Yeah. I'm here. I'm here. and
I'm very interested in meeting.
<i>Hello?</i>

284
00:13:32.645 --> 00:13:34.396
<i>Decker?</i>
Yeah. I'm here. I can hear you.

285
00:13:34.397 --> 00:13:36.565
Can you hear me?
Ma'am?

286
00:13:36.566 --> 00:13:38.734
Ma'am?

287
00:13:49.203 --> 00:13:50.996
<i>What can I say
except it's pretty obvious</i>

288
00:13:50.997 --> 00:13:53.248
<i>there's a serial killer loose
in Fort Lauderdale.</i>

289
00:13:53.249 --> 00:13:57.753
<i>And maybe if the police hadn't
wasted so many resources on me</i>

290
00:13:57.754 --> 00:13:59.421
<i>after he killed Maya.</i>

291
00:13:59.422 --> 00:14:00.839
<i>they would have caught him
back then.</i>

292
00:14:06.429 --> 00:14:08.847
<i>♪ Tres. dos. uno. ja ♪</i>

293
00:14:13.936 --> 00:14:17.147
♪ This ain't the first time
my life has come to this ♪

294
00:14:18.441 --> 00:14:26.741
♪ Ohh ♪

295
00:14:37.752 --> 00:14:41.046
A sinkhole opened up outside
your window three weeks ago

296
00:14:41.047 --> 00:14:42.339
and you didn't come
to stay with us then?

297
00:14:42.340 --> 00:14:44.091
Hi. Catherine.

298
00:14:44.092 --> 00:14:45.635
You know you're the dumbest
ex-husband I ever had?

299
00:14:47.470 --> 00:14:49.304
Palmetto Pastures. RJ?
Seriously?

300
00:14:49.305 --> 00:14:51.390
That's the best you can do?

301
00:14:51.391 --> 00:14:54.351
Well. the price is right. Cath.
What can I say?

302
00:14:54.352 --> 00:14:55.727
If it's a money thing.
you know I don't mind helping.

303
00:14:55.728 --> 00:14:57.437
No. no. no. no. no. no.
no. no. no. no.

304
00:14:57.438 --> 00:14:59.272
It's temporary.
Just like me staying here.

305
00:14:59.273 --> 00:15:00.982
I'll be out of your hair
in no time.

306
00:15:00.983 --> 00:15:02.192
You'll see.

307
00:15:09.033 --> 00:15:12.537
Great. It's great.
Roomy.

308
00:15:14.956 --> 00:15:17.207
How'd your better half
take the news?

309
00:15:17.208 --> 00:15:19.000
Said she wanted
to talk to you.

310
00:15:19.001 --> 00:15:20.001
Mm.

311
00:15:20.002 --> 00:15:21.003
She's in the garage.

312
00:15:27.760 --> 00:15:29.886
You wanted to see me?

313
00:15:29.887 --> 00:15:31.013
One week.

314
00:15:32.390 --> 00:15:33.349
Beg pardon?

315
00:15:36.727 --> 00:15:39.813
You can stay here one week.
and then you go.

316
00:15:39.814 --> 00:15:41.773
Mel. if you think I want to stay
here longer than a week--

317
00:15:41.774 --> 00:15:44.569
One week. felon.
Say it with me.

318
00:15:46.487 --> 00:15:47.446
One week.

319
00:15:49.782 --> 00:15:52.159
No. I won't talk to you
about Clay Gregory.

320
00:15:52.160 --> 00:15:53.410
No. no. no. no. no. no.
I was going to ask about Sofia.

321
00:15:53.411 --> 00:15:55.036
Oh.
Oh. yeah.

322
00:15:55.037 --> 00:15:57.164
She still draining threes
like Steph Curry?

323
00:15:57.165 --> 00:15:59.207
Like Sabrina Ionescu.

324
00:15:59.208 --> 00:16:02.419
And asking about my kid isn't
gonna score you anything.

325
00:16:02.420 --> 00:16:04.921
Just the. uh. the person

326
00:16:04.922 --> 00:16:07.090
who called the police about
the red BMW the other day--

327
00:16:07.091 --> 00:16:09.801
they interacted with the guy
who abandoned it.

328
00:16:09.802 --> 00:16:12.304
Said something. did something.
Am I right?

329
00:16:12.305 --> 00:16:13.723
I just want to know
what they saw.

330
00:16:17.435 --> 00:16:20.312
Maya Gregory was your friend.
I get it.

331
00:16:20.313 --> 00:16:22.981
But this case.
it's about Rhoda Batista.

332
00:16:22.982 --> 00:16:25.483
and it's got enough eyes on it
already.

333
00:16:25.484 --> 00:16:27.819
I don't also need
some pretend P.I.

334
00:16:27.820 --> 00:16:30.405
looking over my shoulder.

335
00:16:30.406 --> 00:16:32.240
let alone one flopping
in my pool house.

336
00:16:32.241 --> 00:16:33.867
You know.

337
00:16:33.868 --> 00:16:35.994
I've started to wonder
if you don't like me

338
00:16:35.995 --> 00:16:37.829
because you're under
the impression

339
00:16:37.830 --> 00:16:39.873
I might be the close-minded type
who'd be embarrassed.

340
00:16:39.874 --> 00:16:42.584
maybe even angry that
his ex-wife ended up marrying

341
00:16:42.585 --> 00:16:44.502
another woman.

342
00:16:44.503 --> 00:16:47.672
Hand to heart. Mel.
it doesn't bother me.

343
00:16:47.673 --> 00:16:49.634
I knew Cath was bi
from day one.

344
00:16:51.344 --> 00:16:52.385
I mean. hell.
we even entertained

345
00:16:52.386 --> 00:16:55.222
the occasional
third party back then.

346
00:16:55.223 --> 00:16:56.890
I got work to do.

347
00:16:56.891 --> 00:16:58.517
Try not to get sent back
to prison today.

348
00:17:02.188 --> 00:17:04.106
<i>¿Intentas infringir
el código?</i>

349
00:17:05.483 --> 00:17:07.943
My Spanish is a little rusty.

350
00:17:07.944 --> 00:17:10.070
You didn't just happen to
confess to murdering two women.

351
00:17:10.071 --> 00:17:11.279
did you?

352
00:17:11.280 --> 00:17:13.448
Decker.
What's it been?

353
00:17:13.449 --> 00:17:16.201
Two years?
18 months with good behavior?

354
00:17:16.202 --> 00:17:19.412
You go to prison one time.
and suddenly it's all the jokes.

355
00:17:19.413 --> 00:17:20.956
I saw your ex's piece
in the <i>Herald</i> this morning.

356
00:17:20.957 --> 00:17:22.999
Oh. yeah?
It's good stuff.

357
00:17:23.000 --> 00:17:24.709
It reminded me of the way
Maya used to write.

358
00:17:24.710 --> 00:17:26.378
All gas. no brakes.

359
00:17:26.379 --> 00:17:27.796
Yeah.
Maya was something. wasn't she?

360
00:17:27.797 --> 00:17:29.381
Before she died--

361
00:17:29.382 --> 00:17:31.174
Before you killed her.
Before she <i>died.</i>

362
00:17:31.175 --> 00:17:34.344
you met me. what. once?
Maybe twice.

363
00:17:34.345 --> 00:17:36.346
You hardly know me.

364
00:17:36.347 --> 00:17:38.181
So how can you be
so sure I killed Maya?

365
00:17:38.182 --> 00:17:39.724
Well. you were
cheating on her.

366
00:17:39.725 --> 00:17:43.520
I was getting away with it.
So why kill my wife?

367
00:17:43.521 --> 00:17:44.771
This new murder. the one
from a couple of days ago--

368
00:17:44.772 --> 00:17:46.481
Rhoda Batista.
That was her name.

369
00:17:46.482 --> 00:17:48.191
She was a teacher. She had
a mom. She had three sisters.

370
00:17:48.192 --> 00:17:50.068
Yeah.
I'm sure you heard by now

371
00:17:50.069 --> 00:17:51.236
I was on an airplane
when it happened.

372
00:17:51.237 --> 00:17:52.862
I didn't do it.
I know you didn't.

373
00:17:52.863 --> 00:17:54.990
Then why are you here?

374
00:17:54.991 --> 00:17:56.908
Would I be right in assuming
that the insurance policy

375
00:17:56.909 --> 00:17:58.577
you had on Maya never paid out?

376
00:17:59.912 --> 00:18:01.746
Of course it didn't.

377
00:18:01.747 --> 00:18:03.748
Because the insurance company.

378
00:18:03.749 --> 00:18:04.833
like pretty much everyone else
in the state of Florida.

379
00:18:04.834 --> 00:18:06.876
knew you killed her.

380
00:18:06.877 --> 00:18:09.754
This new murder. though. I don't
know. maybe it changes things.

381
00:18:09.755 --> 00:18:12.674
Like you said. you were
on a plane when it happened.

382
00:18:12.675 --> 00:18:15.051
You think I hired someone?

383
00:18:15.052 --> 00:18:16.428
Told him to commit
a murder just like Maya's

384
00:18:16.429 --> 00:18:18.054
when I was at 40.000 feet?

385
00:18:18.055 --> 00:18:19.222
Yeah. police start thinking.

386
00:18:19.223 --> 00:18:20.223
"Hey. maybe he didn't
kill his wife."

387
00:18:20.224 --> 00:18:22.392
Then the insurance company.

388
00:18:22.393 --> 00:18:25.687
Suddenly you're. what.
six figures richer? Seven?

389
00:18:25.688 --> 00:18:28.064
This has been fun.
but I've got work to do.

390
00:18:28.065 --> 00:18:30.442
Me too. Clay.
Me too.

391
00:18:40.703 --> 00:18:42.746
Decker Investigations.

392
00:18:42.747 --> 00:18:45.415
<i>Hi. I called last night.
We got cut off.</i>

393
00:18:45.416 --> 00:18:47.292
Hi.
Yes. sorry about that.

394
00:18:47.293 --> 00:18:49.252
I would've called you back.
but your number was blocked.

395
00:18:49.253 --> 00:18:50.587
<i>You're still
up for meeting?</i>

396
00:18:50.588 --> 00:18:52.422
Absolutely.

397
00:18:52.423 --> 00:18:53.298
<i>Then how about we do it
over a drink?</i>

398
00:18:53.299 --> 00:18:55.467
<i>You name the place.</i>

399
00:18:55.468 --> 00:18:57.427
Ooh. Uh. yeah.
Do you know F.M. Station?

400
00:18:57.428 --> 00:18:59.262
<i>I'll find it.
See you at 7:00.</i>

401
00:18:59.263 --> 00:19:00.640
7:00 works. but. um. can I--

402
00:19:02.350 --> 00:19:04.601
Didn't get your name.
Again.

403
00:19:10.483 --> 00:19:11.816
Yes?

404
00:19:11.817 --> 00:19:13.735
Hi. ma'am.
Uh. my name's RJ Decker.

405
00:19:13.736 --> 00:19:15.445
I'm a private investigator.

406
00:19:15.446 --> 00:19:16.529
I-I'd like to ask you
a few questions

407
00:19:16.530 --> 00:19:17.989
about what happened yesterday.

408
00:19:20.076 --> 00:19:22.285
Me? Why me?

409
00:19:22.286 --> 00:19:24.371
Y-You're the one that called
the police. aren't you?

410
00:19:24.372 --> 00:19:26.289
You saw the person
who dumped the car.

411
00:19:26.290 --> 00:19:28.750
If I was. I don't think
the police would tell you.

412
00:19:28.751 --> 00:19:30.585
I knew it was you
from the flower pot.

413
00:19:30.586 --> 00:19:32.754
<i>¿Cómo?</i>
The one you threw
at the suspect.

414
00:19:32.755 --> 00:19:34.881
I saw little pieces of it
on the ground.

415
00:19:36.842 --> 00:19:38.551
See. most of your neighbors.

416
00:19:38.552 --> 00:19:40.136
they like to use
their balconies for storage.

417
00:19:40.137 --> 00:19:42.681
You like to grow things.

418
00:19:42.682 --> 00:19:44.724
Yeah. you must have. what.
a couple dozen plants out there?

419
00:19:44.725 --> 00:19:46.976
So you saw the guy park.
and when he popped the trunk.

420
00:19:46.977 --> 00:19:48.353
you saw what he'd done.

421
00:19:48.354 --> 00:19:49.979
That's why he threw the pot
at him.

422
00:19:49.980 --> 00:19:51.815
All I'm looking for
is a description.

423
00:19:51.816 --> 00:19:54.110
I even brought you a few pots
to replace the ones you broke.

424
00:19:57.238 --> 00:19:58.530
The man was short.

425
00:19:58.531 --> 00:20:00.490
Maybe 5'2". Black.

426
00:20:00.491 --> 00:20:03.118
His back was turned.
so I didn't see his face.

427
00:20:03.119 --> 00:20:05.412
Just his terrible hat.

428
00:20:05.413 --> 00:20:07.122
What was so terrible
about his hat?

429
00:20:07.123 --> 00:20:08.873
There was a penis on it.

430
00:20:08.874 --> 00:20:10.083
Penis?
Did you say penis?

431
00:20:10.084 --> 00:20:11.334
Worse.
An angry penis.

432
00:20:11.335 --> 00:20:13.294
And what made you think
the penis was angry?

433
00:20:13.295 --> 00:20:15.922
The face and the two
little arms flexed like this.

434
00:20:15.923 --> 00:20:17.132
Like it wanted to fight.

435
00:20:17.133 --> 00:20:19.008
Like this?
Mm-hmm.

436
00:20:19.009 --> 00:20:20.552
Huh.

437
00:20:26.517 --> 00:20:29.519
Is this what you saw?
<i>Ay. Dios mio.</i> Yes.

438
00:20:29.520 --> 00:20:31.771
It's not what you think it is.
It's a jumbo shrimp.

439
00:20:31.772 --> 00:20:34.315
Specifically. it's the logo for
the Jacksonville Jumbo Shrimp.

440
00:20:34.316 --> 00:20:36.818
AAA affiliate
to the Miami Marlins.

441
00:20:36.819 --> 00:20:37.986
Does that help?

442
00:20:45.661 --> 00:20:46.871
I like your hat.

443
00:20:47.997 --> 00:20:49.206
Thanks.

444
00:20:52.293 --> 00:20:55.086
What?
No. it's just I wish
I could have seen your face

445
00:20:55.087 --> 00:20:56.796
when you found that dead lady
in the trunk of that car.

446
00:20:58.674 --> 00:21:00.592
Darius.

447
00:21:00.593 --> 00:21:03.386
Hey. kid.
deep breaths. deep breaths.

448
00:21:03.387 --> 00:21:04.972
No need to pull Mom into this.
Come here.

449
00:21:09.477 --> 00:21:11.227
I didn't hurt
that woman. okay?

450
00:21:11.228 --> 00:21:12.520
I'm not a killer.

451
00:21:12.521 --> 00:21:13.771
Well. given she had
about six inches

452
00:21:13.772 --> 00:21:15.732
and 20 pounds on you.
I tend to agree.

453
00:21:15.733 --> 00:21:17.901
The thing is. Darius.
you are a car thief.

454
00:21:17.902 --> 00:21:19.277
And you did
steal that Beemer.

455
00:21:19.278 --> 00:21:21.237
You just didn't know
the first person

456
00:21:21.238 --> 00:21:23.114
who drove it
left the body behind.

457
00:21:23.115 --> 00:21:26.201
Who are you. man?
What is this?

458
00:21:26.202 --> 00:21:28.203
Me? I'm a P.I. Yeah.

459
00:21:28.204 --> 00:21:30.997
As such. I do the occasional job
for an insurance company.

460
00:21:30.998 --> 00:21:32.832
That company insures cars.

461
00:21:32.833 --> 00:21:33.958
and so they keep
pretty meticulous records

462
00:21:33.959 --> 00:21:35.585
when it comes to car thieves.

463
00:21:35.586 --> 00:21:37.086
So I'm on a list.
Yeah. you're on a list.

464
00:21:37.087 --> 00:21:38.588
That's how I found you.

465
00:21:38.589 --> 00:21:40.381
Someone saw the logo
on your hat.

466
00:21:40.382 --> 00:21:41.799
So I checked the list
for car thieves

467
00:21:41.800 --> 00:21:46.012
originally from Jacksonville.
and bam. there you were.

468
00:21:46.013 --> 00:21:48.515
Pinched last year for joyriding
in someone else's Lambo.

469
00:21:48.516 --> 00:21:50.266
I'm a minor.

470
00:21:50.267 --> 00:21:52.352
All that stuff is supposed
to be sealed.

471
00:21:52.353 --> 00:21:54.729
Yeah. well. hey. insurance
companies. what can I say?

472
00:21:54.730 --> 00:21:57.690
I tried to do
the right thing. okay?

473
00:21:57.691 --> 00:22:00.777
I left the car trunk open
so somebody would see the lady.

474
00:22:00.778 --> 00:22:03.905
and the police would arrest
the person who owns the car.

475
00:22:03.906 --> 00:22:05.698
Well.
the person who owns the car

476
00:22:05.699 --> 00:22:08.243
has an alibi described
by Channel 7 as "ironclad."

477
00:22:08.244 --> 00:22:10.411
not to mention zero connection
to the victim.

478
00:22:10.412 --> 00:22:11.746
That's why I think the car
was actually stolen

479
00:22:11.747 --> 00:22:13.289
twice the other night.

480
00:22:13.290 --> 00:22:15.667
first by the killer
and then by you.

481
00:22:15.668 --> 00:22:18.002
What I don't know. what nobody
knows except for you and him

482
00:22:18.003 --> 00:22:20.797
is where the car was
abandoned first.

483
00:22:20.798 --> 00:22:23.299
Where did he leave it
before you stole it?

484
00:22:29.431 --> 00:22:31.266
Hey. hey.

485
00:22:31.267 --> 00:22:33.643
Uncle RJ!
We're making ropa vieja.

486
00:22:33.644 --> 00:22:35.186
Wanna help?
Uh. actually. kiddo.

487
00:22:35.187 --> 00:22:37.647
I need a quick word
with your mom.

488
00:22:37.648 --> 00:22:38.690
and then I have to go
meet a client.

489
00:22:38.691 --> 00:22:40.108
Do you need to bring a gun?

490
00:22:40.109 --> 00:22:41.234
No. sweetie.
I don't even own a gun.

491
00:22:41.235 --> 00:22:42.610
That's 'cause
you can't own a gun.

492
00:22:42.611 --> 00:22:45.488
Can we just. uh. please...

493
00:22:45.489 --> 00:22:49.492
So this guy stole the car
first. dumped it in the lot.

494
00:22:49.493 --> 00:22:51.786
and then the kid you found
stole it a second time?

495
00:22:51.787 --> 00:22:54.664
Yes. He's the one who ended up
in a car chase with police.

496
00:22:54.665 --> 00:22:56.416
But this guy. Popeye Calves.
he's the one

497
00:22:56.417 --> 00:22:58.501
that killed Rhoda Batista.

498
00:22:58.502 --> 00:23:01.337
On orders from Clay Gregory
in order to clear his name.

499
00:23:01.338 --> 00:23:04.132
make a play for Maya's
life insurance money. or both.

500
00:23:04.133 --> 00:23:07.010
All I could get tonight
was video from a hardware store.

501
00:23:07.011 --> 00:23:09.095
But you canvass the area.

502
00:23:09.096 --> 00:23:10.346
maybe you find video
from a different business.

503
00:23:10.347 --> 00:23:12.265
catches Popeye's face.

504
00:23:12.266 --> 00:23:14.143
We find him.
he gives us Clay.

505
00:23:17.688 --> 00:23:18.896
Hey.

506
00:23:21.066 --> 00:23:23.318
Were you sleeping
with Maya Gregory?

507
00:23:23.319 --> 00:23:26.321
I'm asking as a wife.
not a cop.

508
00:23:26.322 --> 00:23:27.864
If it's something
that's going to come out.

509
00:23:27.865 --> 00:23:29.908
I'd rather know now.

510
00:23:29.909 --> 00:23:33.620
No. I wasn't sleeping
with Maya Gregory.

511
00:23:33.621 --> 00:23:35.538
The truth is. I didn't even
know her that well.

512
00:23:35.539 --> 00:23:38.666
She died. this person
you didn't know very well.

513
00:23:38.667 --> 00:23:40.501
and it was. what.
one week later

514
00:23:40.502 --> 00:23:42.671
you lose it on some kid
who breaks into your car?

515
00:23:46.091 --> 00:23:48.426
A few years back. I'm still
working at the <i>Herald.</i>

516
00:23:48.427 --> 00:23:50.053
City Desk sends me out
on what they figured was

517
00:23:50.054 --> 00:23:52.639
a routine drug homicide.

518
00:23:52.640 --> 00:23:54.223
Someone smelled something
awful coming from

519
00:23:54.224 --> 00:23:56.309
the trunk of a car.
called the cops.

520
00:23:56.310 --> 00:23:58.061
I show up just
as they're drilling the locks.

521
00:23:58.062 --> 00:24:00.147
Trunk pops open.

522
00:24:02.107 --> 00:24:03.775
I'm expecting the usual--

523
00:24:03.776 --> 00:24:07.403
gang banger.
no ID. multiple gunshot wounds.

524
00:24:07.404 --> 00:24:09.030
Not a woman with a hanger
wrapped around her neck

525
00:24:09.031 --> 00:24:10.324
and not someone I knew.

526
00:24:12.368 --> 00:24:15.370
Can you guess what I did?
Took her picture.

527
00:24:18.749 --> 00:24:21.584
I'm thinking. "Hey. it's Maya.
It's Maya from work."

528
00:24:21.585 --> 00:24:23.461
But I just keep
bracketing the shots.

529
00:24:23.462 --> 00:24:25.171
changing the angles
to get more of her hair.

530
00:24:25.172 --> 00:24:26.756
but not the face.
not the face.

531
00:24:26.757 --> 00:24:28.383
No. the papers won't
print faces of the dead.

532
00:24:28.384 --> 00:24:29.968
That's policy.

533
00:24:29.969 --> 00:24:31.552
You were doing your job.

534
00:24:31.553 --> 00:24:33.930
Shoot everything.
That's what they expect.

535
00:24:33.931 --> 00:24:35.765
But 9 times out of 10.

536
00:24:35.766 --> 00:24:37.976
they'll only use
your most vanilla pic.

537
00:24:37.977 --> 00:24:40.395
the one that tells the story
but won't upset.

538
00:24:40.396 --> 00:24:41.772
The thing is.
the photographer...

539
00:24:44.525 --> 00:24:46.609
Yeah. he remembers
all of 'em.

540
00:24:46.610 --> 00:24:49.445
The next day. I quit.
I'd had enough.

541
00:24:49.446 --> 00:24:51.823
But then it comes out
that Clay's having an affair.

542
00:24:51.824 --> 00:24:53.574
And I don't know.
I started following him.

543
00:24:53.575 --> 00:24:54.951
I started taking his picture.

544
00:24:57.413 --> 00:25:00.498
I didn't catch him
in the act of anything.

545
00:25:00.499 --> 00:25:02.501
But when I looked at him
through my lens...

546
00:25:03.961 --> 00:25:06.170
...I swear I could see him.

547
00:25:06.171 --> 00:25:09.090
I could see
who he really was.

548
00:25:09.091 --> 00:25:10.883
And my cameras.

549
00:25:10.884 --> 00:25:13.386
all of a sudden.
they were my eyes again.

550
00:25:13.387 --> 00:25:14.887
And they were gonna
help me do something good.

551
00:25:14.888 --> 00:25:17.306
And then stupid Lucas Ochoa

552
00:25:17.307 --> 00:25:19.184
broke into your car
and tried to take them from you.

553
00:25:21.895 --> 00:25:24.313
This new career you picked.

554
00:25:24.314 --> 00:25:26.232
it's hard not to notice
you're still taking pictures.

555
00:25:26.233 --> 00:25:28.526
It's cheating spouses.

556
00:25:28.527 --> 00:25:30.445
guys faking injury to collect
on disability.

557
00:25:30.446 --> 00:25:31.822
For now.

558
00:25:32.990 --> 00:25:34.615
But you stick with it.

559
00:25:34.616 --> 00:25:36.284
and you and I both know

560
00:25:36.285 --> 00:25:38.037
you're gonna start
seeing the ugly stuff again.

561
00:25:39.413 --> 00:25:41.247
Well. I stick with it.

562
00:25:41.248 --> 00:25:42.665
maybe some of the ugly stuff
doesn't happen.

563
00:25:53.343 --> 00:25:55.011
Is she here?
Seated at our finest table.

564
00:25:55.012 --> 00:25:56.096
Okay.

565
00:26:00.684 --> 00:26:02.310
Let me guess.

566
00:26:02.311 --> 00:26:04.188
You're still mad
about the candy bar?

567
00:26:15.199 --> 00:26:17.617
Did you not hear me say
I'm sorry?

568
00:26:17.618 --> 00:26:19.452
Did you not hear me say what you
could do with your apology?

569
00:26:19.453 --> 00:26:21.412
I did.

570
00:26:21.413 --> 00:26:22.955
I assume it's an expression
you learned in prison.

571
00:26:22.956 --> 00:26:24.540
Do you think this is funny?

572
00:26:24.541 --> 00:26:26.542
You think lying
about what happened between me

573
00:26:26.543 --> 00:26:27.835
and your stepbrother. getting
me shipped off to Apalachee

574
00:26:27.836 --> 00:26:30.213
for a year and a half
is some kind of a joke?

575
00:26:30.214 --> 00:26:31.923
No.
but you mess with one Ochoa.

576
00:26:31.924 --> 00:26:32.965
you mess with every Ochoa.

577
00:26:32.966 --> 00:26:34.801
Oh. right.
The Ochoas.

578
00:26:34.802 --> 00:26:36.636
Fort Lauderdale's answer
to the freaking Borgias.

579
00:26:36.637 --> 00:26:38.346
How's your dad. by the way?
Is he gonna run for governor?

580
00:26:38.347 --> 00:26:40.681
Or would that put
too many eyes on him?

581
00:26:40.682 --> 00:26:42.058
Make it too hard for
him to accept all those bribes?

582
00:26:42.059 --> 00:26:43.643
State Senator Ochoa
is very well. thanks.

583
00:26:43.644 --> 00:26:45.353
You know. after that day
in court. I looked you up.

584
00:26:45.354 --> 00:26:46.979
I saw you were one
of his special consultants.

585
00:26:46.980 --> 00:26:48.981
I'm curious. did you tell him
how you consulted me

586
00:26:48.982 --> 00:26:51.317
right before you testified?
Because wow.

587
00:26:51.318 --> 00:26:52.944
Special would be putting it
mildly.

588
00:26:52.945 --> 00:26:54.362
I thought you were gonna
consult my damn legs off.

589
00:26:54.363 --> 00:26:56.614
Can we please talk
about why I called?

590
00:26:56.615 --> 00:26:58.324
If you think I want a job from
you. you're out of your mind.

591
00:26:58.325 --> 00:27:00.284
There is no job.

592
00:27:00.285 --> 00:27:02.370
There is just me
wanting to say I'm sorry.

593
00:27:02.371 --> 00:27:04.580
I thought I should do it
face to face.

594
00:27:04.581 --> 00:27:06.457
but I knew if I didn't pretend
to have work for you.

595
00:27:06.458 --> 00:27:07.875
you wouldn't come.

596
00:27:07.876 --> 00:27:10.086
Are you saying you lied

597
00:27:10.087 --> 00:27:11.295
so you could apologize
for lying?

598
00:27:11.296 --> 00:27:13.005
Tell me I pulled you
away from something.

599
00:27:13.006 --> 00:27:14.590
You heard about the teacher

600
00:27:14.591 --> 00:27:16.217
they found in the trunk
of the car the other day?

601
00:27:16.218 --> 00:27:17.802
I am this close to proving
it was a murder for hire

602
00:27:17.803 --> 00:27:21.138
with the bill footed
by Clay Gregory.

603
00:27:21.139 --> 00:27:25.268
What?
Clay Gregory is like
a Teflon Scott Peterson.

604
00:27:25.269 --> 00:27:27.436
He's this town's
whitest white whale.

605
00:27:27.437 --> 00:27:29.814
And you're gonna--
You?

606
00:27:30.858 --> 00:27:32.483
Tell your dad I said hi.

607
00:27:46.999 --> 00:27:49.333
Hey. What's up?
Hey. where are you?

608
00:27:49.334 --> 00:27:51.752
<i>Trailer.</i>
The one in the crater?

609
00:27:51.753 --> 00:27:54.714
Yeah. The other day. I told Mel
about all the surveillance pics

610
00:27:54.715 --> 00:27:57.258
I took of Clay Gregory
after Maya died.

611
00:27:57.259 --> 00:27:59.844
I figured I'd go through them
again. see if I missed anything.

612
00:27:59.845 --> 00:28:03.014
And?
I'm pretty sure his hairline's
starting to recede.

613
00:28:03.015 --> 00:28:04.682
Yeah. well. I'm heading
to a press conference.

614
00:28:04.683 --> 00:28:06.601
It's supposed to be an update
on Rhoda Batista.

615
00:28:06.602 --> 00:28:07.810
but since I'm sleeping
with the lead detective.

616
00:28:07.811 --> 00:28:09.729
I already got the scoop.

617
00:28:09.730 --> 00:28:10.980
The footage that you found

618
00:28:10.981 --> 00:28:12.773
led to more footage
from a different business

619
00:28:12.774 --> 00:28:14.066
that showed the guy
in the hoodie.

620
00:28:14.067 --> 00:28:16.152
Popeye Calves.
What?

621
00:28:16.153 --> 00:28:18.070
Uh. nothing.
Continue.

622
00:28:18.071 --> 00:28:19.697
It showed him getting into
a silver sedan and driving away.

623
00:28:19.698 --> 00:28:22.116
Bad news is.
the camera was too far away

624
00:28:22.117 --> 00:28:23.951
to give a good look at his face
or his license plate.

625
00:28:23.952 --> 00:28:25.244
Progress is progress.

626
00:28:25.245 --> 00:28:27.079
Go home. okay?

627
00:28:27.080 --> 00:28:28.706
I didn't think that trailer was
safe before the sinkhole.

628
00:28:33.670 --> 00:28:35.379
Hey. Tebow.
How you doing. man?

629
00:28:35.380 --> 00:28:37.340
Movin' on
from the clown thing?

630
00:28:37.341 --> 00:28:38.883
Good for you.
Sorta five years ago.

631
00:28:41.887 --> 00:28:42.929
Tebow?

632
00:29:26.348 --> 00:29:28.433
Tom Petty just saved my life.

633
00:29:33.271 --> 00:29:34.647
Park's clear. No sign of
the guy who shot at you.

634
00:29:34.648 --> 00:29:36.190
Yeah. it was Popeye Calves.

635
00:29:36.191 --> 00:29:37.650
You saw his legs?
No. I didn't need to.

636
00:29:37.651 --> 00:29:39.277
I paid Clay a visit.
I told him I knew

637
00:29:39.278 --> 00:29:40.528
he hired someone
to commit a murder

638
00:29:40.529 --> 00:29:42.154
that looked just like Maya's.

639
00:29:42.155 --> 00:29:43.739
Obviously. he called Popeye.
told him I had to go.

640
00:29:43.740 --> 00:29:45.658
but this is good.
Clay's getting sloppy.

641
00:29:45.659 --> 00:29:47.285
Not only did Popeye
fail to kill me--

642
00:29:47.286 --> 00:29:48.995
No. he left blood evidence.
his gun.

643
00:29:48.996 --> 00:29:50.663
and God knows
what else behind.

644
00:29:50.664 --> 00:29:52.498
Any of it gives us a name.
Clay's as good as done.

645
00:29:59.589 --> 00:30:01.549
I told RJ he was welcome
to still stay with us.

646
00:30:01.550 --> 00:30:03.217
but he wouldn't hear it.

647
00:30:03.218 --> 00:30:05.094
Someone tried
to kill him tonight.

648
00:30:05.095 --> 00:30:06.637
Your doorstep is the last place

649
00:30:06.638 --> 00:30:08.556
he'd want to bring
that much danger.

650
00:30:08.557 --> 00:30:10.433
And your doorstep's okay?

651
00:30:10.434 --> 00:30:12.268
You know me and RJ's story.
don't you?

652
00:30:12.269 --> 00:30:14.478
You were cellmates
at Apalachee.

653
00:30:14.479 --> 00:30:18.108
Huh. Okay.
That all he told you?

654
00:30:20.193 --> 00:30:21.236
Well...

655
00:30:23.363 --> 00:30:26.574
When your ex and I met.
I was doing a stretch

656
00:30:26.575 --> 00:30:29.118
for holding up
a convenience store in Coral.

657
00:30:29.119 --> 00:30:32.455
But the thing is.
I was innocent.

658
00:30:32.456 --> 00:30:34.623
A common refrain
around Apalachee. mind you.

659
00:30:34.624 --> 00:30:36.667
"I'm innocent."

660
00:30:36.668 --> 00:30:39.796
And yet. in my case.
it was the God's honest truth.

661
00:30:42.591 --> 00:30:44.592
RJ was the only one
who believed me.

662
00:30:44.593 --> 00:30:46.427
He wasn't a P.I. yet.

663
00:30:46.428 --> 00:30:47.970
but he got himself
a contraband phone

664
00:30:47.971 --> 00:30:50.222
and started looking into it.

665
00:30:50.223 --> 00:30:52.641
Made some calls.
sent some e-mails.

666
00:30:52.642 --> 00:30:54.643
chipped away
at the State's case.

667
00:30:54.644 --> 00:30:57.021
and finally he was
able to prove the robbery

668
00:30:57.022 --> 00:30:59.356
was the work
of someone else

669
00:30:59.357 --> 00:31:01.484
and the perpetrator
just happened to leave the scene

670
00:31:01.485 --> 00:31:03.819
in a vehicle that looked
remarkably like mine.

671
00:31:03.820 --> 00:31:05.446
They only arrested you

672
00:31:05.447 --> 00:31:06.572
'cause you had
the same kind of car?

673
00:31:06.573 --> 00:31:08.491
Well. that and

674
00:31:08.492 --> 00:31:10.493
I'd also robbed other
convenience stores in the past.

675
00:31:10.494 --> 00:31:13.371
The point is.
I was exonerated.

676
00:31:13.372 --> 00:31:18.501
But because the gears
of justice grind slowly.

677
00:31:18.502 --> 00:31:21.712
it amounted to me being released
just one day earlier

678
00:31:21.713 --> 00:31:23.381
than I would have.

679
00:31:23.382 --> 00:31:25.674
So RJ didn't
really change much after all.

680
00:31:25.675 --> 00:31:29.678
He changed
everything...

681
00:31:29.679 --> 00:31:31.138
'cause the very first thing
I did

682
00:31:31.139 --> 00:31:33.474
was I bought a scratcher.

683
00:31:33.475 --> 00:31:36.769
And that scratcher paid
out a million bucks.

684
00:31:36.770 --> 00:31:40.315
and that million bucks
bought me this bar.

685
00:31:44.861 --> 00:31:47.697
I'm not released this day
instead of the next...

686
00:31:49.282 --> 00:31:51.075
...who knows
what becomes of me?

687
00:32:02.212 --> 00:32:03.587
Uncle RJ...
Mm-hmm.

688
00:32:03.588 --> 00:32:05.047
...do you have
any pencils in here?

689
00:32:05.048 --> 00:32:07.174
I have to do my homework.

690
00:32:07.175 --> 00:32:08.509
I was picking her up from school
when you called.

691
00:32:08.510 --> 00:32:10.344
What do you got?
Remember how I told you

692
00:32:10.345 --> 00:32:11.345
I spent some time following Clay
after Maya was killed?

693
00:32:11.346 --> 00:32:13.180
Mm-hmm.

694
00:32:13.181 --> 00:32:14.432
Well. last night
before Popeye Calves showed up.

695
00:32:14.433 --> 00:32:16.225
I was going over some
of my old photos.

696
00:32:16.226 --> 00:32:18.854
and I remembered this guy.

697
00:32:19.938 --> 00:32:21.814
Why do I recognize him?

698
00:32:21.815 --> 00:32:23.566
Probably because
you've driven behind a city bus

699
00:32:23.567 --> 00:32:25.568
sometime in the last 15 years.

700
00:32:25.569 --> 00:32:26.986
That's where he does most
of his advertising.

701
00:32:26.987 --> 00:32:29.572
Ah.
Sleazy Plastic Surgeon Guy.

702
00:32:29.573 --> 00:32:30.990
Yeah. with the name
that sounds made-up.

703
00:32:30.991 --> 00:32:32.616
Yep.
Dr. Adrian Noble.

704
00:32:32.617 --> 00:32:34.493
That's his practice over there.

705
00:32:34.494 --> 00:32:36.620
Turns out Adrian Noble
was not his real name.

706
00:32:36.621 --> 00:32:39.498
It's actually Cecil Gregory.
As in Clay Gregory.

707
00:32:39.499 --> 00:32:40.958
They're related?

708
00:32:40.959 --> 00:32:42.543
Cousins. And get this--
back in 2020.

709
00:32:42.544 --> 00:32:45.004
old Cecil tried opening
a second office in Miami.

710
00:32:45.005 --> 00:32:46.589
Did not go well.

711
00:32:46.590 --> 00:32:48.382
He was losing money
hand over fist.

712
00:32:48.383 --> 00:32:50.217
Or at least he was until
an electrical fire broke out

713
00:32:50.218 --> 00:32:52.428
and the whole place
burned down.

714
00:32:52.429 --> 00:32:54.388
He walked away with
a seven-figure insurance payout.

715
00:32:54.389 --> 00:32:55.931
An electrical fire.

716
00:32:55.932 --> 00:32:57.016
And Clay's
a commercial electrician.

717
00:32:57.017 --> 00:32:58.934
If you were a total sleaze

718
00:32:58.935 --> 00:33:00.728
and your cousin helped you
bilk an insurance company

719
00:33:00.729 --> 00:33:03.063
out of a million bucks.
what wouldn't you do for him?

720
00:33:03.064 --> 00:33:05.191
Okay. so you think Adrian Noble
isn't just Cecil Gregory.

721
00:33:05.192 --> 00:33:06.609
he's Popeye Calves. too.

722
00:33:06.610 --> 00:33:08.068
Yeah. All we have to do
is look for

723
00:33:08.069 --> 00:33:10.321
Tom Petty's bite marks
on his legs.

724
00:33:10.322 --> 00:33:12.239
The guy who sings
"Free Fallin'" bit someone?

725
00:33:12.240 --> 00:33:13.825
No. sweetie.
Tom Petty's a dog now.

726
00:33:16.828 --> 00:33:18.871
